an></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/x2IKPrE</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[cannibalthemusical]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Crispy buffalo tofu bites recipe!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/pdFY6P7</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/RYZOlxd.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>https://www.triedandtruerecipe.com/vegan-buffalo-tofu-bites/

Sweet potato starch makes for really delicious, crispy tofu! If you don’t keep vegan, use traditional butter and honey instead!!!

Sweet potato starch is used commonly in Taiwanese fried chicken (usually as a coating for the second fry IIRC)- I don’t know if it’s the higher moisture content but something about it gets bubbly and gooey and creates a really delicious, crispy exterior. I use it for frying alllll the time. So good!

1 pound extra-firm tofu (pressed and cut into 1-inch cubes)
1 teaspoon salt
⅓ cup sweet potato starch or use cornstarch 
2 tablespoons neutral oil
½ cup Frank’s RedHot Hot Sauce or your preferred cayenne-based hot sauce. 
2 tablespoons vegan butter (use dairy if you don’t keep vegan)
2 tablespoons vegan honey or maple syrup (more or less to taste, depending on heat preference) (use traditional honey if you don’t keep vegan)
2 scallions (trimmed and minced)

Prepare the tofu:
Place the cubed tofu in a large bowl and sprinkle with salt.

Pour the sweet potato starch on top and gently coat it with the flour using a rubber spatula. Avoid breaking the tofu too much. You can also shake the bowl around to ensure the tofu is coated.

Fry the tofu:
Heat the neutral oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat until very hot. Turn the heat to medium once the oil shimmers. Be sure to allow the oil to preheat for 5 minutes.

Add the tofu in an even layer–frying in batches if needed–and cook without moving for 3–4 minutes per side. Turn only when the tofu releases easily from the bottom of the skillet. If your oil was nice and hot when you added the tofu, it shouldn’t stick. Cook until all the tofu is golden brown and crispy. Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate.

Prepare the sauce:
While you wait for the oil to preheat, combine Frank’s RedHot Hot Sauce in a saucepan with vegan butter and honey. Turn the heat to medium-high and bring to a low boil. Remove from heat and set aside.

Sauce the tofu bites:
Transfer the tofu to a large bowl and pour the sauce on top. Toss gently to combine.

To serve:
Transfer the tofu bites to a large plate. Sprinkle with minced scallions, and enjoy!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/v3KSCZK.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I was really proud of how these turned out especially because the sweet potato starch held up really well to the sauce!! Next time I’m gonna try air frying them and see if the sweet potato starch gets as crispy in the air fryer as it does the skillet.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/pdFY6P7</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[triedandtruerecipes]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I has fisk. Is my fisk!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/JVpLRWc</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/4n8XMLf.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/JVpLRWc</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[vladrichdemaclant]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>NEVER GIVE UP !!!!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/D7DJD4h</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/63YgOUk.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Finally, there's gonna be a transfer of "The Killer" that does look like it was ripped from a VCR in 1996

